Wait, `input` is an array of size 2! `struct scatterlist input[2];`
`input->length` checks `input[0].length`. But what if the SG list returned by `zs_obj_read_sg_begin` has 2 entries?
Wait, if `entry->length == PAGE_SIZE`, can it be spanning 2 entries in the zsmalloc pool?
Actually, `zs_obj_read_sg_begin` fills the `input` SG list.
If `entry->length == PAGE_SIZE`, it means the original object length is exactly a full page.
In `zsmalloc`, objects can span multiple pages. So a PAGE_SIZE object can indeed span 2 pages, meaning `input[0].length` wouldn't be `PAGE_SIZE`, it would be less than `PAGE_SIZE`, and `input[1].length` would have the rest!
