If it spans 2 pages, `input[0].length` would be `< PAGE_SIZE`, and `WARN_ON_ONCE` would trigger!
But wait, let's see how `zs_obj_read_sg_begin` initializes the SG list.
Does `zs_obj_read_sg_begin` guarantee that a `PAGE_SIZE` object will be in a single SG entry?
`zsmalloc` typically stores objects of `PAGE_SIZE` in huge classes. A huge class object has `size == PAGE_SIZE`.
Huge classes in zsmalloc are never spanning multiple pages! They occupy exactly one full page.
So `input[0].length` will be `PAGE_SIZE` because zsmalloc allocates exactly one page for a huge object, and it doesn't span pages.
