    "content": "{"content":"Documentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-278-\t\t\t\t通常很重要的是，如果你推迟刷新，实际的刷新发生在同一个\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-279-\t\t\t\tCPU上，因为它将cpu存储到页面上，使其变脏。同样，请看\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-280-\t\t\t\tsparc64关于如何处理这个问题的例子。\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-281-\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst:282:  ``void flush_dcache_folio(struct folio *folio)``\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-283-\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-284-\t该函数的调用情形与flush_dcache_page()相同。它允许架构针对刷新整个\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-285-\tfolio页面进行优化，而不是一次刷新一页。\nDocumentation/translations/zh_CN/core-api/cachetlb.rst-286-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-272-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-273-\tIf D-cache aliasing is not an issue, these two routines may\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-274-\tsimply call memcpy/memset directly and do nothing more.\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-275-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst:276:  ``void flush_dcache_folio(struct folio *folio)``\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-277-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-278-        This routines must be called when:\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-279-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-280-\t  a) the kernel did write to a page that is in the page cache page\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-281-\t     and / or in high memory\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-282-\t  b) the kernel is about to read from a page cache page and user space\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-283-\t     shared/writable mappings of this page potentially exist.  Note\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst:284:\t     that {get,pin}_user_pages{_fast} already call flush_dcache_folio\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-285-\t     on any page found in the user address space and thus driver\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-286-\t     code rarely needs to take this into account.\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-287-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-288-\t.. note::\n--\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-312-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-313-\tThis allows these interfaces to be implemented much more\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-314-\tefficiently.  It allows one to \"defer\" (perhaps indefinitely) the\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-315-\tactual flush if there are currently no user processes mapping this\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst:316:\tpage.  See sparc64's flush_dcache_folio and update_mmu_cache_range\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-317-\timplementations for an example of how to go about doing this.\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-318-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst:319:\tThe idea is, first at flush_dcache_folio() time, if\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-320-\tfolio_flush_mapping() returns a mapping, and mapping_mapped() on that\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-321-\tmapping returns %false, just mark the architecture private page\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-322-\tflag bit.  Later, in update_mmu_cache_range(), a check is made\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-323-\tof this flag bit, and if set the flush is done and the flag bit\n--\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-350-  unsigned long vmaddr)``\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-351-\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-352-  \tWhen the kernel needs to access the contents of an anonymous\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-353-\tpage, it calls this function (currently only\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst:354:\tget_user_pages()).  Note: flush_dcache_folio() deliberately\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-355-\tdoesn't work for an anonymous page.  The default\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-356-\timplementation is a nop (and should remain so for all coherent\nDocumentation/core-api/cachetlb.rst-357-\tarchitectures).  For incoherent architec